description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about delivering high standards of nursing, with an interest in palliative and end of life care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit enthusiastic Registered Nurses who want to make a difference to join our established Community Team. Working in the local community, this role will give you the opportunity to deliver individualised holistic evidence-based nursing care to patients and those important to them&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main duties will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Supporting those who wish to die in their own homes by undertaking urgent and routine assessment visits to those facing the end of their life&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Coordinate and plan care utilising a range of services, such as, Hospice at Home, District Nursing and Marie Curie etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Working collaboratively with patients and their families, and other health care professionals to provide shared patient care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Undertaking symptom control and personal care, and provide immediate support to the patient and their family&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Recognise signs of dying to enable discussion with patients and families regarding choices at end of life, to initiate anticipatory prescribing so that symptoms can be addressed in a timely way&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be required to demonstrate your abilities in the following areas:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· First level Registered General Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Ability to assess, provide and evaluate high standards of care without supervision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Be organised and have strong decision-making skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Ability to supervise unqualified staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Understanding of the issues affecting patients and families at the end of life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Good holistic assessment skills and symptom management knowledge. However, applicants will be supported with their own learning and development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Capability to work remotely and flexibly&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work a variable shift pattern between the hours of 08.00 and 20.00 over 7 days. You will receive an unsocial hour’s enhancement for weekend and bank holiday working. All candidates must have a full clean driving license and have access to a car.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal discussion please contact Dr Matt Sweeting, Director of Care at matt.sweeting@farleighhospice.org&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to working with you in the future&lt;/p&gt;
